{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this was just one of these miracles, then, that seemed to happen in war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "If we'd have been five minutes earlier, she'd have been five minutes later, we might never have seen Eve again.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I don't know whether she would eventually have made her way back to Holland and, and England, because she had, did have a birth certificate in her name.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And maybe she would've been found eventually somewhere, because she was in Leipzig, so she was in America, in American zone.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "If she had stayed in the Russian zone-- But the Birnbaums had brought them all over to the Leipzig [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So I think we would've met her again, but nevertheless, it was remiss of us to have forgotten about her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And anyway-- but we saw her on this truck, and we stopped the other truck.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we got to Eve to transfer to our truck, and she came with us on a train back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I suppose we were surprised [LAUGHS] and shocked and amazed, and, and, you know, forgotten all about her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was probably [NON-ENGLISH] who had spotted her or noticed her, and, and we got her and said goodbye to the Birnbaums and all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These are, again, people who went off to Israel afterwards, and, and because we forgot all about the Holocaust and all that, we, we never said thank you to the Birnbaums.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And now they're dead.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We, we-- somebody sent us their address a few years ago, but meanwhile they've died.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So there are lots of things that we should have done that we haven't done.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We took Eve with us on the train-- cattle truck, it was another great, big, long train of cattle trucks.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
